<script type="text/template" id="list-messages-template">
  <li>
    <div class="message_path">
      <span class="messages_left_path">
        <img src="images/abdu-avatar.png" alt="" />
      </span>
      <span class="messages_middle_path">
        <# if (current_user.username == from){ #>

        <a href=""><#= to #></a>

        <# } else { #>

        <a href=""><#= from #></a>

        <# } #>
        <span class="new_message"><#= subject #></span>
      </span>
      <div class="messages_right_path">
        <a href="" class="count_read_message_new">3 Messages</a>
        <span>.</span>
        <span class="count_read_message"><abbr class="timeago" title="<#= created_at #>"></abbr></span>
        <div class="action_menu_hide">
          <ul>
            <li>
              <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="reply_hide">
                <label>reply</label>
                <span class="reply_icon">&nbsp;</span>
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="delete_hide">
                <label>delete</label>
                <span class="delete_icon">&nbsp;</span>
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="mark_read_hide">
                <label>mark as read</label>
                <span class="mark_icon">&nbsp;</span>
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="no_padding_right messages_down_arrow">&nbsp;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="reply_message_path">
      <p class="greeting">Hello,</p>
      <p>How can I define a message with a string field longer than 512 characters?</p>
      <p>
        When defining a field as a String in a Message Definition, I am finding that the resulting type in 
        Oracle is an nvarchar(255) which is too small for my application needs. According to the Tracking Server documentation, the "element may be any ASCII string." 
        I see options in Tracking Server for "String64", "String256" and "String512", 
        so it would seem that "String" would be unbounded or at least larger than 512 characters.
      </p>
      <p>Thanks,</p>
      <ul id="reply_message" class="reply_message">
        <li>
          <div class="photo_reply_message">
            <span class="no_margin_left messages_left_path">
              <img src="images/avatar-metrofx.png" alt="" />
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="contents_reply_message">
            <span class="messages_middle_path">
              <a href="" class="me">You</a>
              <span class="read_message">Re: How are you?</span>
            </span>
            <span class="messages_right_path">
              <a href="" class="count_read_message">replied 6 hours ago</a>
            </span>
            <p>
              It appears that *all* string types (String, String64, String256, String512) are being created as nvarchar2(255) in Oracle. (?!) In other words, apparently it's not possible to log a message with a string field longer than 255 characters using the Tracking Server feature loggers.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="photo_reply_message">
            <span class="no_margin_left messages_left_path">
              <img src="images/sarah-avatar.png" alt="" />
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="contents_reply_message">
            <span class="messages_middle_path">
              <a href="">Sarah</a>
              <span class="read_message">Re: How are you?</span>
            </span>
            <span class="messages_right_path">
              <a href="" class="count_read_message">replied 3 minutes ago</a>
            </span>
            <p>
              This has been confirmed as a defect. The Tracking Team is working on releasing the fix to be part of Tracking Server 10 SP1. I'll have to check with the team if they will also release
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <div class="replay_path">
        <div class="photo_reply_message">
          <span class="reply_text">Reply</span>
          <form action="/messages/<#= _id #>/reply.json" method="post" class="message-reply-form">
            <span class="input_replay">
              <span class="reply_message_photo no_margin_left messages_left_path">
                <img src="images/avatar-metrofx.png" alt="" />
                <input name="authenticity_token" type="hidden" value=<%= form_authenticity_token %> />
              </span>
              <span class="textarea_reply">
                <span class="triangle_inbox">&nbsp;</span>
                <textarea name="content" rows="" cols=""></textarea>
              </span>
            </span>
            <%= submit_tag "", :style => "display: none" %>
            <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="replay_button">Reply</a>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </li>
</script>
